// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion Intergrations 3/Flux Tech Sheet.txt
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Technical Sheet: Fusion Flux1. Internal ArchitectureFlux operates as a multi-pass static analysis tool.Pass 1: Manifest Parsing. Validates Fusion.toml against the Target Runtime Capability Matrix (TRCM).Pass 2: AST Analysis. Uses regex-based heuristic scanning (v1) and syn-based AST traversal (v2) to identify forbidden patterns (e.g., std::fs in async blocks).Pass 3: FFI Verification. cross-references extern "C" definitions in Rust with header files defined in the manifest.2. PerformanceScan Speed: ~150ms per 10k LoC.Memory Footprint: < 50MB.3. Error CodesCodeSeverityDescriptionE001CriticalRuntime Target Mismatch (e.g., Python in v1).E002CriticalBlocking I/O in Async Context.E003ErrorUnsafe FFI Boundary (Missing #[no_mangle]).E004ErrorSandbox Breach (Host calls in strict Nebula).E005ErrorWasm Leak (Wasm modules in Native v1).E006ErrorLegacy Crypto Usage (RSA/AES detected).
